\mt1 TIMOTHY  
\c 1  
\s1 Greeting  
\m
\v 1 \w Paul|strong="G3972"\w*, \w an|strong="G1722"\w* apostle \w of|strong="G1223"\w* \w Jesus|strong="G2424"\w* \w Christ|strong="G5547"\w* \w by|strong="G1223"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w will|strong="G2307"\w* \w of|strong="G1223"\w* \w God|strong="G2316"\w*, \w according|strong="G2596"\w* \w to|strong="G2596"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w promise|strong="G1860"\w* \w of|strong="G1223"\w* \w life|strong="G2222"\w*\f + \fr 1:1 \ft The “life that is in Christ Jesus”—that is what it is all about. As He Himself said, “I have come that they may have life, and that they may have it more abundantly” (John 10:10).\f* \w that|strong="G3588"\w* \w is|strong="G3588"\w* \w in|strong="G1722"\w* \w Christ|strong="G5547"\w* \w Jesus|strong="G2424"\w*,\f + \fr 1:1 \ft The going back and forth between “Jesus Christ” and “Christ Jesus” appears to be merely a matter of style.\f*  
\v 2 \w to|strong="G2532"\w* dear \w son|strong="G5043"\w* \w Timothy|strong="G5095"\w*: \w Grace|strong="G5485"\w*, \w mercy|strong="G1656"\w*, \w peace|strong="G1515"\w* \w from|strong="G1515"\w* \w God|strong="G2316"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w Father|strong="G3962"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w Christ|strong="G5547"\w* \w Jesus|strong="G2424"\w* \w our|strong="G2316"\w* \w Lord|strong="G2962"\w*.   
\ms1 Paul addresses Timothy's spiritual crisis  
\s1 Paul encourages Timothy  
\p
\v 3 \w I|strong="G1473"\w* \w give|strong="G1473"\w* \w thanks|strong="G5485"\w* \w to|strong="G2532"\w* \w God|strong="G2316"\w*, \w whom|strong="G3739"\w* \w I|strong="G1473"\w* \w serve|strong="G3000"\w* \w with|strong="G1722"\w* \w a|strong="G2192"\w* \w clear|strong="G2513"\w* \w conscience|strong="G4893"\w* \w like|strong="G5613"\w* \w my|strong="G1722"\w* \w forefathers|strong="G4269"\w* \w did|strong="G2532"\w*,\f + \fr 1:3 \ft So why does Paul bring his ancestors into the picture? I suppose to set up a parallel with Timothy and his ancestors (verse 5). One's heritage is important.\f* \w as|strong="G5613"\w* \w I|strong="G1473"\w* constantly \w remember|strong="G2192"\w* \w you|strong="G4771"\w* \w in|strong="G1722"\w* \w my|strong="G1722"\w* \w prayers|strong="G1162"\w*, \w night|strong="G3571"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w day|strong="G2250"\w*,  
\v 4 \w longing|strong="G1971"\w* \w to|strong="G2443"\w* \w see|strong="G3708"\w* \w you|strong="G4771"\w* (recalling \w your|strong="G3708"\w* \w tears|strong="G1144"\w*),\f + \fr 1:4 \ft From what follows I take it that Timothy was going through a spiritual crisis when Paul last saw him, hence the tears. Paul did what he could to help, but is anxious to know how Timothy is doing.\f* \w that|strong="G2443"\w* \w I|strong="G2443"\w* \w may|strong="G2443"\w* \w be|strong="G2443"\w* \w filled|strong="G4137"\w* \w with|strong="G4137"\w* \w joy|strong="G5479"\w*;  
\v 5 \w while|strong="G1722"\w* \w I|strong="G2532"\w* \w call|strong="G2532"\w* \w to|strong="G2532"\w* \w mind|strong="G2532"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* unfeigned \w faith|strong="G4102"\w* \w that|strong="G3754"\w* \w is|strong="G3588"\w* \w in|strong="G1722"\w* \w you|strong="G4771"\w*—\w it|strong="G2532"\w* resided \w first|strong="G4413"\w* \w in|strong="G1722"\w* \w your|strong="G2532"\w* \w grandmother|strong="G3125"\w* \w Lois|strong="G3090"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w in|strong="G1722"\w* \w your|strong="G2532"\w* \w mother|strong="G3384"\w* \w Eunice|strong="G2131"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w*, \w I|strong="G2532"\w* \w am|strong="G2532"\w* \w persuaded|strong="G3982"\w*, \w in|strong="G1722"\w* \w you|strong="G4771"\w* \w also|strong="G2532"\w*.  
\v 6 \w For|strong="G1223"\w* \w this|strong="G3588"\w* \w reason|strong="G1223"\w* \w I|strong="G1473"\w* \w am|strong="G1510"\w* reminding \w you|strong="G4771"\w* \w to|strong="G1722"\w* rekindle\f + \fr 1:6 \ft Timothy had received a ‘charisma’ from God through Paul, but the verb “rekindle” indicates clearly that the use of the gift is up to him, and he has been neglecting it.\f* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w gift|strong="G5486"\w* \w of|strong="G1223"\w* \w God|strong="G2316"\w* \w which|strong="G3739"\w* \w is|strong="G1510"\w* \w in|strong="G1722"\w* \w you|strong="G4771"\w* \w through|strong="G1223"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w laying|strong="G1936"\w* \w on|strong="G1722"\w* \w of|strong="G1223"\w* \w my|strong="G1722"\w* \w hands|strong="G5495"\w*.  
\v 7 \w Because|strong="G1063"\w* \w God|strong="G2316"\w* \w did|strong="G2532"\w* \w not|strong="G3756"\w* \w give|strong="G1325"\w* \w us|strong="G1325"\w* \w a|strong="G2532"\w* \w spirit|strong="G4151"\w* \w of|strong="G4151"\w* cowardice,\f + \fr 1:7 \ft Timothy must not retreat, must not give up; rather he should make use of the resources God has placed at his disposal—and so should we. Anytime we are attacked by fear, we may calculate that it is not from God.\f* \w but|strong="G2532"\w* \w of|strong="G4151"\w* \w power|strong="G1411"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w of|strong="G4151"\w* love \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w of|strong="G4151"\w* \w self-control|strong="G4995"\w*.   
\s1 Don't be ashamed to suffer for Christ  
\p
\v 8 \w So|strong="G3767"\w* \w do|strong="G3361"\w* \w not|strong="G3361"\w* \w be|strong="G3361"\w* \w ashamed|strong="G1870"\w* \w to|strong="G2596"\w* identify \w with|strong="G2316"\w* \w our|strong="G2316"\w* \w Lord|strong="G2962"\w* \w or|strong="G3366"\w* \w with|strong="G2316"\w* \w me|strong="G1473"\w* \w His|strong="G2596"\w* \w prisoner|strong="G1198"\w*, \w but|strong="G3361"\w* \w join|strong="G4777"\w* \w in|strong="G2596"\w* \w suffering|strong="G4777"\w* \w for|strong="G2316"\w* \w the|strong="G2596"\w* \w Gospel|strong="G2098"\w* \w according|strong="G2596"\w* \w to|strong="G2596"\w* \w the|strong="G2596"\w* \w power|strong="G1411"\w* \w of|strong="G2316"\w* \w God|strong="G2316"\w*\f + \fr 1:8 \ft Living out the Gospel in this world has everything to do with the power of God.\f*  
\v 9 —\w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w One|strong="G3588"\w* \w who|strong="G3588"\w* \w saved|strong="G4982"\w* \w us|strong="G1325"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w called|strong="G2564"\w* \w us|strong="G1325"\w* \w with|strong="G1722"\w* \w a|strong="G2532"\w* holy \w calling|strong="G2821"\w*, \w not|strong="G3756"\w* \w because|strong="G1722"\w* \w of|strong="G2532"\w* \w our|strong="G2424"\w* \w works|strong="G2041"\w* \w but|strong="G2532"\w* \w because|strong="G1722"\w* \w of|strong="G2532"\w* \w His|strong="G1722"\w* \w own|strong="G2398"\w* \w purpose|strong="G4286"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w grace|strong="G5485"\w*, \w which|strong="G3588"\w*\f + \fr 1:9 \ft It is hard to determine whether the pronoun refers only to “grace” or to both “purpose and grace”.\f* \w was|strong="G3588"\w* \w given|strong="G1325"\w* \w to|strong="G2532"\w* \w us|strong="G1325"\w* \w in|strong="G1722"\w* \w Christ|strong="G5547"\w* \w Jesus|strong="G2424"\w* \w before|strong="G4253"\w* \w time|strong="G5550"\w* began,\f + \fr 1:9 \ft Really; the Lamb's blood was shed before this world was created (1 Peter 1:19-20).\f*  
\v 10 \w but|strong="G1161"\w* \w has|strong="G5547"\w* \w now|strong="G1161"\w* \w been|strong="G2532"\w* \w revealed|strong="G5319"\w* \w through|strong="G1223"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w appearing|strong="G2015"\w* \w of|strong="G1223"\w* \w our|strong="G2424"\w* \w Savior|strong="G4990"\w*, \w Jesus|strong="G2424"\w* \w Christ|strong="G5547"\w*, \w who|strong="G3588"\w* \w by|strong="G1223"\w* \w means|strong="G1223"\w* \w of|strong="G1223"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w Gospel|strong="G2098"\w* \w destroyed|strong="G2673"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w death|strong="G2288"\w*\f + \fr 1:10 \ft That is what the Text says, “the death”; I take it that the reference is to Satan's kingdom. Indeed, is that not what Hebrews 2:14-15 declares? “Since, then, the children have flesh and blood as their share, He Himself likewise partook of the same, in order that through His death He might abolish the one who had the power of death—that is, the devil—and set free these [the children] who during their whole lifetime were subject to slavery through fear of death.” See also 1 John 3:8.\f* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w brought|strong="G5461"\w* \w life|strong="G2222"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* immortality \w to|strong="G2532"\w* \w light|strong="G5461"\w*;  
\v 11 \w to|strong="G1519"\w* \w this|strong="G3739"\w* Gospel \w I|strong="G1473"\w* \w was|strong="G3739"\w* \w appointed|strong="G5087"\w* \w as|strong="G1519"\w* \w a|strong="G2532"\w* proclaimer, \w an|strong="G2532"\w* apostle \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w a|strong="G2532"\w* \w teacher|strong="G1320"\w* \w of|strong="G2532"\w* nations.\f + \fr 1:11 \ft About 1% of the Greek manuscripts, of objectively inferior quality, omit “of nations” (as in NIV, NASB, LB, TEV, etc.).\f*  
\v 12 \w That|strong="G3754"\w* \w is|strong="G1510"\w* \w why|strong="G1223"\w* \w I|strong="G1473"\w* \w am|strong="G1510"\w* \w suffering|strong="G3958"\w* \w these|strong="G3778"\w* \w things|strong="G3778"\w*, \w yet|strong="G2532"\w* \w I|strong="G1473"\w* \w am|strong="G1510"\w* \w not|strong="G3756"\w* \w ashamed|strong="G1870"\w* \w because|strong="G3754"\w* \w I|strong="G1473"\w* \w know|strong="G1492"\w* \w in|strong="G1519"\w* \w whom|strong="G3739"\w* \w I|strong="G1473"\w* \w have|strong="G2532"\w* \w believed|strong="G4100"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w am|strong="G1510"\w* \w certain|strong="G2532"\w* \w that|strong="G3754"\w* \w He|strong="G2532"\w* \w is|strong="G1510"\w* \w able|strong="G1415"\w* \w to|strong="G1519"\w* \w guard|strong="G5442"\w* \w my|strong="G1473"\w* deposit\f + \fr 1:12 \ft That is right, “my deposit”; by dying to himself and living for Christ's kingdom he is building up a ‘savings account’ in Heaven.\f* \w until|strong="G1519"\w* \w that|strong="G3754"\w* \w Day|strong="G2250"\w*.\f + \fr 1:12 \ft The Day when we face God's bar and give an accounting (see verse 18 below).\f*   
\s1 Be loyal—the example of Onesiphorus  
\p
