\v 6 —\w the|strong="G3588"\w* hardworking \w farmer|strong="G1092"\w* \w should|strong="G1163"\w* \w be|strong="G1163"\w* \w the|strong="G3588"\w* \w first|strong="G4413"\w* \w to|strong="G1163"\w* \w receive|strong="G3335"\w* \w of|strong="G3588"\w* \w the|strong="G3588"\w* \w fruits|strong="G2590"\w*.\f + \fr 2:6 \ft I believe the verse could be just as well translated as, ‘the hardworking farmer must first receive of the fruits’, the point being that he has to have seed before he can plant the subsequent crop.\f*  
\v 7 Ponder \w what|strong="G3739"\w* \w I|strong="G3739"\w* \w am|strong="G3588"\w* \w saying|strong="G3004"\w*; \w may|strong="G3956"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w Lord|strong="G2962"\w* \w indeed|strong="G1063"\w* \w give|strong="G1325"\w* \w you|strong="G4771"\w* \w understanding|strong="G4907"\w* \w in|strong="G1722"\w* \w it|strong="G1063"\w* \w all|strong="G3956"\w*.\f + \fr 2:7 \ft To succeed requires commitment, dedication, whether you are a soldier, an athlete or a farmer.\f*   
\s1 Encouragement by example  
\p
\v 8 Keep \w thinking|strong="G3421"\w* \w of|strong="G1537"\w* \w Jesus|strong="G2424"\w* \w Christ|strong="G5547"\w*, \w raised|strong="G1453"\w* \w from|strong="G1537"\w* \w the|strong="G1537"\w* \w dead|strong="G3498"\w*, \w of|strong="G1537"\w* \w David|strong="G1138"\w*'s \w seed|strong="G4690"\w*; \w this|strong="G3588"\w* \w is|strong="G3588"\w* \w my|strong="G1473"\w* \w gospel|strong="G2098"\w*,\f + \fr 2:8 \ft This brief statement evokes much of the essence of the Gospel. “David's seed” recalls that the Creator really became human, with David's genes, and fulfills the prophecies about the Messiah. “Raised from the dead” recalls everything connected with His death and resurrection. Thinking about Jesus is a good antidote to discouragement.\f*  
\v 9 \w for|strong="G1722"\w* \w which|strong="G3739"\w* \w I|strong="G3739"\w* \w am|strong="G1210"\w* \w suffering|strong="G2553"\w* \w to|strong="G1722"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w point|strong="G3360"\w* \w of|strong="G3056"\w* \w being|strong="G1722"\w* \w in|strong="G1722"\w* \w chains|strong="G1199"\w* \w like|strong="G5613"\w* \w a|strong="G5613"\w* \w criminal|strong="G2557"\w*, \w but|strong="G2316"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w Word|strong="G3056"\w* \w of|strong="G3056"\w* \w God|strong="G2316"\w* \w is|strong="G3588"\w* \w not|strong="G3756"\w* chained.  
\v 10 \w This|strong="G3778"\w* \w is|strong="G3588"\w* \w why|strong="G1223"\w* \w I|strong="G2532"\w* \w endure|strong="G5278"\w* \w it|strong="G2532"\w* \w all|strong="G3956"\w*: \w for|strong="G1223"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w sake|strong="G1223"\w* \w of|strong="G1223"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w chosen|strong="G1588"\w* ones,\f + \fr 2:10 \ft They are “chosen” but Paul has to suffer so that they may obtain. See 2 Corinthians 1:5-7, Philippians 3:10, Colossians 1:24 and 1 Peter 4:13.\f* \w that|strong="G2443"\w* \w they|strong="G2532"\w* \w also|strong="G2532"\w* \w may|strong="G2532"\w* \w obtain|strong="G5177"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w salvation|strong="G4991"\w* \w that|strong="G2443"\w* \w is|strong="G3588"\w* \w in|strong="G1722"\w* \w Christ|strong="G5547"\w* \w Jesus|strong="G2424"\w*, \w with|strong="G3326"\w* eternal \w glory|strong="G1391"\w*.  
\v 11 \w This|strong="G3588"\w* \w is|strong="G3588"\w* \w a|strong="G2532"\w* \w trustworthy|strong="G4103"\w* \w word|strong="G3056"\w*:  
\q1 \w If|strong="G1487"\w*, \w indeed|strong="G2532"\w*, \w we|strong="G1063"\w* \w died|strong="G4880"\w* \w together|strong="G2532"\w*,\f + \fr 2:11 \ft We must really identify with Christ's death, which involves commitment and a change of life, a change of worldview.\f*  
