\p
\v 16 \w At|strong="G1722"\w* \w my|strong="G1722"\w* \w first|strong="G4413"\w* defense \w no|strong="G3762"\w* \w one|strong="G3762"\w* \w came|strong="G3854"\w* \w to|strong="G1722"\w* help \w me|strong="G1473"\w*, \w but|strong="G3361"\w* \w all|strong="G3956"\w* \w deserted|strong="G1459"\w* \w me|strong="G1473"\w*. \w May|strong="G3956"\w* \w it|strong="G3588"\w* \w not|strong="G3361"\w* \w be|strong="G3361"\w* held \w against|strong="G1722"\w* \w them|strong="G3588"\w*.\f + \fr 4:16 \ft Note the difference in attitude toward these people and toward the coppersmith in verse 14.\f*  
\v 17 \w But|strong="G1161"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w Lord|strong="G2962"\w* \w stood|strong="G3936"\w* \w by|strong="G1223"\w* \w me|strong="G1473"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w strengthened|strong="G1743"\w* \w me|strong="G1473"\w*, \w so|strong="G2443"\w* \w that|strong="G2443"\w* \w through|strong="G1223"\w* \w me|strong="G1473"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w message|strong="G2782"\w* \w might|strong="G2532"\w* \w be|strong="G2532"\w* \w fully|strong="G4135"\w* proclaimed \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w all|strong="G3956"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w nations|strong="G1484"\w* \w might|strong="G2532"\w* hear.\f + \fr 4:17 \ft I suppose that Paul wrote some of his letters after this first trial, and thus “the nations” are still ‘hearing’.\f* \w Also|strong="G2532"\w*, \w I|strong="G1473"\w* \w was|strong="G3588"\w* \w delivered|strong="G4506"\w* \w out|strong="G1537"\w* \w of|strong="G1537"\w* \w a|strong="G2532"\w* \w lion|strong="G3023"\w*'\w s|strong="G2962"\w* \w mouth|strong="G4750"\w*;\f + \fr 4:17 \ft I suppose this is literal; someone tried to have him condemned to face a lion in the arena, but the plan was foiled.\f*  
\v 18 \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w Lord|strong="G2962"\w* \w will|strong="G2532"\w* \w deliver|strong="G4506"\w* \w me|strong="G1473"\w* \w from|strong="G2532"\w* \w every|strong="G3956"\w* \w evil|strong="G4190"\w* \w work|strong="G2041"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w save|strong="G4982"\w* \w me|strong="G1473"\w* \w into|strong="G1519"\w* \w His|strong="G3956"\w* \w heavenly|strong="G2032"\w* Kingdom;\f + \fr 4:18 \ft To get \+bd into\+bd* the “heavenly Kingdom” is the goal.\f* \w to|strong="G1519"\w* \w whom|strong="G3739"\w* \w be|strong="G2532"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w glory|strong="G1391"\w* \w for|strong="G1519"\w* \w ever|strong="G1519"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w ever|strong="G1519"\w*. Amen.   
\s1 Farewell  
\p
\v 19 Greet \w Prisca|strong="G4251"\w*\f + \fr 4:19 \ft It is generally considered that ‘Prisca’ is an alternate spelling, or shortened form, for ‘Priscilla’.\f* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* Aquila, \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w household|strong="G3624"\w* \w of|strong="G2532"\w* \w Onesiphorus|strong="G3683"\w*.  
