\p
\v 22 \w The|strong="G3588"\w* \w Lord|strong="G2962"\w* \w Jesus|strong="G2962"\w* \w Christ|strong="G2962"\w*\f + \fr 4:22 \ft Perhaps 3% of the Greek manuscripts omit “Jesus Christ” (as in NIV, NASB, LB, TEV, etc.).\f* \w be|strong="G3588"\w* \w with|strong="G3326"\w* \w your|strong="G2962"\w* \w spirit|strong="G4151"\w*. \w The|strong="G3588"\w* \w Grace|strong="G5485"\w*\f + \fr 4:22 \ft ‘Grace’ occurs with the definite article = ‘the grace’; so I capitalized it.\f* \w be|strong="G3588"\w* \w with|strong="G3326"\w* \w you|strong="G5210"\w*.\f + \fr 4:22 \ft “Your spirit” is singular, referring to Timothy, but the “you” here is plural—I take it that Paul knew the letter would be read by others.\f* Amen.   